<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 05 at 6:29PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Heavy snow showers will impact portions of Fergus County through
715 PM MDT...
At 626 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking heavy snow showers 9 miles
west of Geyser, or 23 miles west of Stanford, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Visibility less than a half mile due to heavy snow.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Highly variable road conditions.
Locations impacted include...
Stanford, Geyser and Raynesford.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Use extreme caution if traveling in this area.</instruction>
